{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"init_"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"cancellable","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV","text":"CancellableRef","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableRef"},{"text":"? = nil) ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"throws"},{"kind":"text","text":" -> "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","level":2,"anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This method is intended for language bindings. If writing in C,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_initable_new()"},{"text":" should typically be used instead.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The object must be initialized before any real use after initial","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"construction, either with this function or ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_async_initable_init_async()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Implementations may also support cancellation. If ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cancellable"},{"type":"text","text":" is not "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"then initialization can be cancelled by triggering the cancellable object"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"from another thread. If the operation was cancelled, the error"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"cancelled","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" will be returned. If "},{"code":"cancellable","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is not ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":" and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the object doesn’t support cancellable initialization the error"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"notSupported"},{"type":"text","text":" will be returned."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If the object is not initialized, or initialization returns with an"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"error, then all operations on the object except "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_ref()"},{"type":"text","text":" and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"g_object_unref()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" are considered to be invalid, and have undefined","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"behaviour. See the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"#iface@Gio.Initable#description"},{"type":"text","text":" for more details."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Callers should not assume that a class which implements "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Initable","isActive":true},{"text":" can be","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"initialized multiple times, unless the class explicitly documents itself as"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"supporting this. Generally, a class’ implementation of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"init()"},{"text":" can assume","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(and assert) that it will only be called once. Previously, this documentation","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"recommended all ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Initable","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" implementations should be idempotent; that"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"recommendation was relaxed in GLib 2.54.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If a class explicitly supports being initialized multiple times, it is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"recommended that the method is idempotent: multiple calls with the same"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"arguments should return the same results. Only the first call initializes","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the object; further calls return the result of the first call."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"One reason why a class might need to support idempotent initialization is if"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"it is designed to be used via the singleton pattern, with a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"GObjectClass.constructor","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" that sometimes returns an existing instance.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"In this pattern, a caller would expect to be able to call ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_initable_init()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"on the result of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_new()"},{"type":"text","text":", regardless of whether it is in fact a new"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"instance."}]}]}],"abstract":[{"text":"Initializes the object implementing the interface.","type":"text"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/MemoryMonitorRef","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/MemoryMonitorRef\/InitableProtocol-Implementations"]]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/memorymonitorref\/init_(cancellable:)"]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"sections":[],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/MemoryMonitorRef\/init_(cancellable:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"externalID":"s:3GIO16InitableProtocolPAAE5init_11cancellableSbAA14CancellableRefVSg_tKF::SYNTHESIZED::s:3GIO16MemoryMonitorRefV","title":"init_(cancellable:)","extendedModule":"GIO","roleHeading":"Instance Method","role":"symbol","symbolKind":"method","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"init_"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"cancellable","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"CancellableRef","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV"},{"kind":"text","text":"?) "},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"}]},"kind":"symbol","references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO":{"type":"topic","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","title":"GIO","url":"\/documentation\/gio","role":"collection","kind":"symbol"},"https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/hadess/low-memory-monitor/":{"type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"Low Memory Monitor","type":"text"}],"url":"https:\/\/gitlab.freedesktop.org\/hadess\/low-memory-monitor\/","title":"Low Memory Monitor","identifier":"https:\/\/gitlab.freedesktop.org\/hadess\/low-memory-monitor\/"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/Initable":{"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/initable","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Initable","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"Initable","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Initable","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GInitable"},{"type":"text","text":" is implemented by objects that can fail during"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"initialization. If an object implements this interface then","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"it must be initialized as the first thing after construction,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"either via [method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.Initable.init"},{"text":"] or [method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.AsyncInitable.init_async"},{"type":"text","text":"]"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(the latter is only available if it also implements [iface","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncInitable","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"])."}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Initable"}]},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/CancellableRef":{"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"CancellableRef","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"CancellableRef","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableRef","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/cancellableref","abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GCancellable"},{"type":"text","text":" allows operations to be cancelled."}],"title":"CancellableRef"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/MemoryMonitorRef/InitableProtocol-Implementations":{"kind":"article","abstract":[],"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/memorymonitorref\/initableprotocol-implementations","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/MemoryMonitorRef\/InitableProtocol-Implementations","title":"InitableProtocol Implementations","role":"collectionGroup","type":"topic"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/AsyncInitable":{"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncInitable","title":"AsyncInitable","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/asyncinitable","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"AsyncInitable","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"AsyncInitable","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","abstract":[{"code":"GAsyncInitable","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is an interface for asynchronously initializable objects."}]},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/MemoryMonitorRef/init_(cancellable:)":{"role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/memorymonitorref\/init_(cancellable:)","abstract":[{"text":"Initializes the object implementing the interface.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/MemoryMonitorRef\/init_(cancellable:)","title":"init_(cancellable:)","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"init_"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"cancellable","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"CancellableRef"},{"text":"?) ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"throws"},{"kind":"text","text":" -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool"}]},"https://hadess.pages.freedesktop.org/low-memory-monitor/":{"type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"API documentation","type":"text"}],"url":"https:\/\/hadess.pages.freedesktop.org\/low-memory-monitor\/","title":"API documentation","identifier":"https:\/\/hadess.pages.freedesktop.org\/low-memory-monitor\/"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/MemoryMonitorRef":{"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/memorymonitorref","kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"MemoryMonitorRef","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"code":"GMemoryMonitor","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" will monitor system memory and suggest to the application"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"when to free memory so as to leave more room for other applications."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"It is implemented on Linux using the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/gitlab.freedesktop.org\/hadess\/low-memory-monitor\/","isActive":true},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"("},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/hadess.pages.freedesktop.org\/low-memory-monitor\/"},{"text":").","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MemoryMonit